<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Destined" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Destined,</orth> doomed or ordained by fate: <cit><quote>the d. ill she must herself assay,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 156" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 156</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>being d. to a drier death,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.158" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 1, 158</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>putting on the d. livery,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.4.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 4, 138</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>d. to a fairer death,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.219" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 219</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>take thou the d. tenth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 4, 33</bibl></cit>.
<pb n="301" />
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>